[1] China (Hong Kong - imported)
Date: 14 Jan 2005
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Department of Health, Hong Kong 14 Jan 2005 [edited]
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/2005/Jan/050114e.htm>

Dengue fever update
--------------------
The Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Department of Health
confirmed an imported case of dengue fever and urged people to guard
against the disease. Case details are as follows:
Age: 30
Sex: Male
District of residence: Yuen Long
Date of Onset: 4 Dec 2004
Symptoms: Fever, headache and eye pain
Present Condition: No hospitalization required.
Recovered.
Travel History: Traveled to Bangladesh in December 2004 before onset of
symptoms. [See ref. (30) below for suspected cases in Bangladesh in
September 2004. - Mod.JW]
Cumulative Total in 2004: 31
* imported: 31
* local: 0
