[3] Ecuador (Manabi)
Date: Sat 15 Jan 2005
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@orange.net>
Source: Prensa Latina, 7 Jan 2005 [in Spanish, summarized & edited by Mod.JW]
<http://www.prensa-latina.org/article.asp?ID=8B89A25E-9BAD-4FE4-B32E-7597BC7796FF&language=ES>

Official sources report an outbreak of 4 cases of DHF in less than 2 weeks
in Manabi province, western Ecuador. The 2 most recent cases are
hospitalized in Guayaquil, the economic capital of the country. One is a
6-year-old child, from Chone canton, admitted to the hospital on 4 Jan
2005, and now out of danger. The other is a woman aged 43, from the same
area, who became ill on 23 Dec 2004 and was transferred to Guayaquil on 30
Dec 2004.
Another case was a 48-year-old man from Manabi, who was discharged this
week [2nd week of January 2005], and the 4th was a 10-year-old child from
Portoviejo, also in Manabi,
The regional authority says that these cases bring to 10 the total number
of DHF cases seen in Manabi in 2004.
--
Pablo Nart
<p.nart@orange.net>
