[4] El Salvador
Date: Sun 16 Jan 2005
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Epidemiological Bulletin of Dengue, Ministry of Health, El Salvador
[in Spanish, summarized & edited by Mod.JW]
<http://www.mspas.gob.sv/vigi_epide2005/dengue2005.pdf>

For epidemiological week one of 2005, the Ministry of Heath of El Salvador
reports a total of 92 confirmed cases of dengue, with no cases of DHF or
deaths. (For the same week of 2004, the total was 50 confirmed cases,
including 3 of DHF, with no deaths). The department with the highest
incidence of cases was San Salvador (the capital) with 45 percent of the cases.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[For the previous report on ProMED, see ref. (25) below. Although the
number of cases is almost double that of the same time in 2004, the totals
are too small to be able to say there is an epidemic brewing. - Mod.JW]
