[7] Malaysia 1999-2004
Date: 14 Jan 2005
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Bernama.com, Malaysia [edited]
<http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v3/news_lite.php?id=114520>

361 dengue deaths recorded over last 6 years
-----------------------------------------------
A total of 361 people died of dengue fever out of 130 673 cases reported
since 1999, Health Ministry Disease Control Division Director Dr. Ramlee
Rahmat said Friday [14 Jan 2005]. He said the total did not include the
latest death reported in the 2nd week of this year [2005]. Of the last 6
years, 2002 recorded the highest number of dengue cases and deaths (99), he
told reporters here Friday.
Based on Health Ministry statistics,
- a total of 37 deaths were recorded in 1999 from 10 146 cases reported,
- 45 died in 2000 (7146),
- 50 people in 2001 (16 368),
- 99 in 2002 from (32 767),
- 72 in 2003 (31 043)
- 58 in 2004 (33 203).
He said the number deaths and cases reported in Malaysia remained at a low
level compared with several neighbors, including Thailand and Singapore.
The tourism sector need not worry, as the ministry was constantly
monitoring the situation, he said. He added that the disease could be
contained if everyone played their part, including continuously destroying
larvae breeding areas.
--
